building music.  He swallowed the lump forming in his throat and then he turned his full attention to Hippolyte, &quot;I suppose that I should not overstay my welcome.  Perhaps it would be best if I left the ceremony now.  I'll be staying in the tavern, even though Delerium has offered me the guest hut for the evening.  I do not wish to be treated special simply because I am the queen's son.&quot;  He had not expected that being the queen's son would have brought with it such a feeling of frustration.  He wanted to be his own man, but it was becoming more and more apparent that as long as he stayed here in Themiscrya, in the shadow of his powerful mother, then that would most likely not be possible. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alexiares>Alexiares</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#993300>(5/25/03 8:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=83>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Casual Glances</span><hr size=1> The drums stopped their beating for a moment.  Making Alexiares stop her dancing and take the time to look around at the others.  She stopped her eyes upon De'Lerium for a moment and wondered when the ceremony was going to begin.  Then her eyes glanced over to Hippolyte who was with Theseus.  She smiled remembering meeting him in Troy.  The dancer walked over to greet him.  As she neared, Alexiares asked, &quot;I hope that I am not intruding upon anything.  But, I wanted to say hello to the son of Vasilissa Hippolyte.&quot;  She smiled and nodded in respect to the Queen and then looked to Theseus. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theseusofthemiscrya>Theseus of Themiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#993300>(5/25/03 8:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=84>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Greeting the Dancer</span><hr size=1> Theseus smiled at Alexiares, a warm familiar smile, &quot;It's a pleasure to see you here again, Alexi.&quot;  He bowed politely to her, shaking her hand with the traditional warrior's handshake.  &quot;I can certainly see why the goddess would want you as a dancer in her temple.  You're movements are mesmerizing and enrapturing.&quot;  He glanced to his mother, hoping that she did not continue to hover too long.  &quot;I trust that you've met my mother, Hippolyte.&quot;  He glanced to Hippolyte ready to make an introduction if need be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alexiares>Alexiares</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#993300>(5/25/03 9:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=85>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Greeting the Dancer</span><hr size=1> Alexiares smiled with an almost blush.  She had been complimented before  on her dancing.  But something in his compliment felt different.  When he mentioned Hippolyte, Alexiares turned and looked to the Queen.  &quot;Yes, there is no need to introduce one of the great queens of the Amazon Nation.  The Goddess was with me the day that your mother found the roman encampment that had enslaved me and many other women.  I will be eternally greatful.&quot;   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=theseusofthemiscrya>Theseus of Themiscrya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#993300>(5/25/03 9:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=472.topic&index=86>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Fraternizing with Temple Dancers</span><hr size=1> The amazon prince smiled at the dancer, his eyes moving to her bare mid-drift.  He swallowed the lump in his throat, &quot;Are you thirsty? Can I get you something to drink?&quot;  He moved to the table where the punch was and poured himself a cup of punch, then he went ahead and poured some for Alexi.  &quot;So you were enslaved by the Romans?  Tell me about that.  That is definitely something that I need to learn more about.  I did not realize that the Romans actually had slaves.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gi