ree with an eye for an eye. She had this murderous wench slowly tourtured by the hands of Moranna untill this night. After all, it was Moranna's art to tourture without killing, she thrived on it.<br>
<br>
Walking up to the Queen's viewing stand, she smiled noting the sacrifice sitting on the raft in the water, struggling with what little strength she had left, but o no avail. DeLerium turned and looked to the gathered amazons.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sisters, tonight we send this pathetic excuse for a woman into Poseidon's icy grasp. Tonight we celebrate the end of this life, who so visiously and for no good reason, took the life of one of our sisters. In the divine name of Artemis we offer this sacrifice to her, in thanks for our strength, our power as women. Never to bend our knees for the males sake. Artemis has showed us our own path, and along this path, we have learned that mercy for our enemy, is for the weak. We will never let one get away with harming our own.&quot;<br>
<br>
She motioned for the archer Lisana to come to her. Lisana lit the cloth at the tip of her arrow and handed the bow and arrow to DeLerium. Holding both up, DeLerium looked back to the crowd.<br>
<br>
&quot;In the name of Artemis, Patroness of the Amazons, Goddess of the Moon and Hunt, we offer this sacrifice to you.&quot;<br>
<br>
She turned back to the river and aimed the flamming arrow towards the watery tart who bobbed on the raft, sending the arrow straight into the woman's thigh, DeL smiled, it was not a killing spot, she wanted the woman to suffer badly. Lisana handed her another flamming arrow, and DeL aimed for the other thigh, hitting her target perfectly. She let out a cry of victory and watched the flames grow.:: <p>Vasilissa apo o Adelfi Themiscrya<br>
